I'm sure that life would be a lot easier if everybody agreed on the name of
your host.  If you're currently calling it both A and B, in different contexts,
and if you can't stop calling it B, then stop calling it A.  Change the
official name.  If ``handies'' is the name you can change, stop calling it
``handies.''

(If you can arrange to keep the timeout periods such that properly-timed-out
records don't advertise cname(handies)=ncar and cname(ncar)=handies
simultaneously, so much the better.)

MXs can't point to CNAMEs--check RFC974--but NSs and everything else can,
certainly for a short transition period.

                Craig Everhart
                Andrew message system

